From: Jakub Kicinski <kuba@kernel.org>
Date: Mon, 18 Oct 2021 14:10:03 -0700
Subject: ethernet: ocelot: use eth_hw_addr_gen()
Patch-mainline: v5.16-rc1
Git-commit: 53fdcce6ab932dbd8f1df75873b6f303dc85751f
References: jsc#PED-1565

Commit 406f42fa0d3c ("net-next: When a bond have a massive amount
of VLANs...") introduced a rbtree for faster Ethernet address look
up. To maintain netdev->dev_addr in this tree we need to make all
the writes to it got through appropriate helpers.

Signed-off-by: Jakub Kicinski <kuba@kernel.org>
Reviewed-by: Vladimir Oltean <vladimir.oltean@nxp.com>
Signed-off-by: David S. Miller <davem@davemloft.net>
Acked-by: Thomas Bogendoerfer <tbogendoerfer@suse.de>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/mscc/ocelot_net.c |    3 +--
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 2 deletions(-)

--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/mscc/ocelot_net.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/mscc/ocelot_net.c
@@ -1495,8 +1495,7 @@ int ocelot_probe_port(struct ocelot *oce
 		NETIF_F_HW_TC;
 	dev->features |= NETIF_F_HW_VLAN_CTAG_FILTER | NETIF_F_HW_TC;
 
-	eth_hw_addr_set(dev, ocelot->base_mac);
-	dev->dev_addr[ETH_ALEN - 1] += port;
+	eth_hw_addr_gen(dev, ocelot->base_mac, port);
 	ocelot_mact_learn(ocelot, PGID_CPU, dev->dev_addr,
 			  ocelot_port->pvid_vlan.vid, ENTRYTYPE_LOCKED);
 
